You have to get the angle right.

00:17:22.731 --> 00:17:23.774
Who are you?

00:17:24.232 --> 00:17:25.484
Me?

00:17:26.234 --> 00:17:27.319
I...

00:17:29.196 --> 00:17:30.405
I'm...

00:17:32.074 --> 00:17:35.202
Oh, this guy, Ji Dong-man.

00:17:35.285 --> 00:17:38.580
- I'm his friend.
- The big bearded guy?

00:17:38.664 --> 00:17:42.042
Yes, that's right.
And he's so loud when he chews.

00:17:42.334 --> 00:17:43.710
He got discharged yesterday.

00:17:44.670 --> 00:17:45.837
Oh, really?

00:17:47.047 --> 00:17:51.510
He didn't say anything about leaving
when I spoke to him on the phone.

00:17:52.344 --> 00:17:53.720
Hey, look at me.

00:17:56.723 --> 00:17:59.059
Man, he's not picking up.

00:17:59.977 --> 00:18:02.396
That's too bad.
I can't bring these apples back.

00:18:03.647 --> 00:18:05.941
Put them here. They look heavy.

00:18:06.024 --> 00:18:07.484
Yes, put them over here.

00:18:07.818 --> 00:18:08.860
Sure.

00:18:09.194 --> 00:18:11.989
You two can share.
You must eat well to get better soon.

00:18:14.408 --> 00:18:15.492
My goodness.

00:18:16.618 --> 00:18:18.662
These apples are top-notch.

00:18:18.912 --> 00:18:21.915
Right? You know your apples.

00:18:21.999 --> 00:18:26.295
I gave some to a friend,
and he said all apples were the same.

00:18:26.586 --> 00:18:29.673
- Thank you.
- I run a grocery store

00:18:29.881 --> 00:18:32.926
and can tell an apple's Brix
just by its color.

00:18:33.010 --> 00:18:34.511
A grocery store.

00:18:35.637 --> 00:18:38.557
No wonder you have a good eye.

00:18:39.391 --> 00:18:42.644
By the way, how did you two end up here?

00:18:42.894 --> 00:18:46.023
Me? You know, an accident.

00:18:46.106 --> 00:18:47.691
Right, an accident.

00:18:49.568 --> 00:18:50.611
And you, Mr. Grocery Store?

00:18:51.903 --> 00:18:55.240
You know, a car accident.

00:19:02.789 --> 00:19:04.374
You have to find the right point.

00:19:04.458 --> 00:19:08.754
Now that I've found it,
my shoulder is suddenly in so much pain.

00:19:08.837 --> 00:19:10.213
No way.

00:19:11.298 --> 00:19:13.258
How's that possible? You're lying.

00:19:13.342 --> 00:19:15.677
- No, I'm not.
- Liar.

00:19:15.761 --> 00:19:17.220
- I don't believe you.
- No.

00:19:18.138 --> 00:19:20.182
I didn't believe him at first, either.

00:19:20.265 --> 00:19:23.435
But I did as he told me, and it worked.

00:19:23.518 --> 00:19:25.145
Really?

00:19:25.979 --> 00:19:27.105
How long have you been here for?

00:19:27.481 --> 00:19:29.691
It's been about three months for me.

00:19:29.775 --> 00:19:33.070
I've moved between hospitals,
depending on where it hurts.

00:19:33.695 --> 00:19:36.698
Master, how can you change where it hurts?

00:19:36.782 --> 00:19:38.533
Show me your ways.

00:19:39.076 --> 00:19:41.620
- Are you curious?
- Yes, we are!

00:19:41.703 --> 00:19:42.871
Absolutely.

00:19:44.122 --> 00:19:46.083
Okay, so...

00:19:50.462 --> 00:19:52.089
Why am I getting a call?

00:19:53.632 --> 00:19:55.717
Excuse me. I have to take this.

00:19:55.801 --> 00:19:57.427
Don't share your secret until I'm back.

00:19:57.511 --> 00:19:59.930
- I'm curious, too.
- Just take the call here.

00:20:00.681 --> 00:20:01.515
Okay.

00:20:02.808 --> 00:20:05.018
What now? This is an important moment.

00:20:05.102 --> 00:20:07.521
Every moment I've worked with you
has felt very important.

00:20:07.604 --> 00:20:08.939
When I first met you, I--

00:20:09.022 --> 00:20:10.524
Are you confessing your love to me?

00:20:10.899 --> 00:20:12.985
I'm married, so are you sure?

00:20:13.068 --> 00:20:13.902
What?

00:20:15.487 --> 00:20:19.157
Whatever.
There's a Kim Su-il at that hospital.

00:20:20.617 --> 00:20:21.827
KIM **-IL

00:20:22.744 --> 00:20:25.122
Is he a witness? Okay.

00:20:27.291 --> 00:20:29.042
Really?

00:20:29.751 --> 00:20:31.545
I passed by there.

00:20:32.921 --> 00:20:34.006
Okay.

00:20:39.386 --> 00:20:41.305
- That's funny.
- How's the apple?

00:20:48.061 --> 00:20:49.187
Honey...

00:20:50.522 --> 00:20:53.317
I told you
to get the scratch on your face treated.

00:20:54.443 --> 00:20:55.652
But here you are, hospitalized.

00:20:56.361 --> 00:20:58.572
Are you in a lot of pain?

00:20:59.031 --> 00:21:02.618
That's too bad.
We've got deliveries backed up.

00:21:03.535 --> 00:21:05.162
Honey, it's not what you think.

00:21:05.954 --> 00:21:08.457
Car accidents lead to trauma.

00:21:08.540 --> 00:21:09.833
Car accidents?

00:21:09.958 --> 00:21:11.918
I wasn't the driver,

00:21:12.002 --> 00:21:15.881
but I dove into a huge fire of ashes
to save others--

00:21:15.964 --> 00:21:16.923
A huge fire?

00:21:18.550 --> 00:21:19.468
I...

00:21:19.551 --> 00:21:20.802
Mr. Kim Su-il.

00:21:21.553 --> 00:21:25.140
You're the witness of the collision
at the Kiyun Intersection earlier, right?

00:21:26.183 --> 00:21:27.351
Who are you?

00:21:29.311 --> 00:21:32.022
Oh, I'm from Veotigo Insurance.

00:21:32.397 --> 00:21:34.733
I'm Choi Kang of the SIU Team. Here.

00:21:35.233 --> 00:21:36.735
What does "SIU" stand for?

00:21:36.818 --> 00:21:40.030
"Special Investigation Unit,"

00:21:40.113 --> 00:21:42.574
so, a unit that conducts
special investigations.

00:21:42.658 --> 00:21:44.952
Oh, my back!

00:21:45.911 --> 00:21:48.956
I deal with people who are in pain
whenever they see me,

00:21:49.039 --> 00:21:52.209
as well as fake diagnoses,
overtreatment, and fraudulent claims.

00:21:52.292 --> 00:21:54.711
I do all sorts of things
to investigate these cases.

00:21:55.587 --> 00:21:58.256
Sir, it's too late. I recorded everything.

00:21:58.799 --> 00:22:01.259
So, you're saying
Veotigo Insurance is here

00:22:01.343 --> 00:22:04.554
to compensate
for the scar on my husband's face?

00:22:04.805 --> 00:22:07.391
We'll have to discuss the details later,

00:22:07.766 --> 00:22:09.643
but basically, yes.

00:22:09.977 --> 00:22:14.189
But before that, he must tell us in detail
what happened on site.

00:22:14.273 --> 00:22:16.316
Let me say one thing before that.

00:22:17.109 --> 00:22:19.194
I'm getting him discharged now,

00:22:19.278 --> 00:22:22.739
so we'd just like
a fair amount of compensation.

00:22:22.823 --> 00:22:25.117
I'll nurse him back to good health

00:22:25.200 --> 00:22:28.370
and make sure he doesn't complain
about neck pain or anything later.

00:22:28.996 --> 00:22:31.039
Honey, my neck really does hurt.

00:22:31.123 --> 00:22:32.958
But I think I'm all good now.

00:22:35.752 --> 00:22:36.628
Okay.

00:22:37.379 --> 00:22:38.755
You were on site, right?

00:22:40.590 --> 00:22:42.884
- Yes.
- What happened?

00:22:43.593 --> 00:22:45.429
So much happened.

00:22:46.179 --> 00:22:50.017
I don't know where to begin or end.

00:22:50.100 --> 00:22:52.728
From how you snuck out at night
to drink your brains out?

00:22:54.730 --> 00:22:55.689
All right.

00:22:56.607 --> 00:22:59.276
So, my buddy, Byeong-nam...

00:24:01.713 --> 00:24:03.423
Gosh, hot.

00:24:04.132 --> 00:24:05.884
Oh, man.

00:24:08.553 --> 00:24:09.513
Here.

00:24:14.267 --> 00:24:15.143
No way.

00:24:15.894 --> 00:24:17.604
Can it corner properly now?

00:24:17.688 --> 00:24:20.941
It was off-balance because it was old.
I just added some weight in the front.

00:24:22.401 --> 00:24:23.402
That's sick.

00:24:24.152 --> 00:24:26.280
- You're sick, sir.
- Sick?

00:24:27.364 --> 00:24:29.241
- You ate this up.
- Ate this?

00:24:29.574 --> 00:24:30.784
Eat what?

00:24:31.702 --> 00:24:35.122
Anyway, I fixed the balance,
but come back if it's still not good.

00:24:36.498 --> 00:24:38.000
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

00:24:38.083 --> 00:24:39.876
- Goodbye.
- Have a good day.

00:24:40.836 --> 00:24:43.297
August, 2025...

00:24:44.923 --> 00:24:47.467
Byeong-nam, come out! It's your bro!

00:24:48.552 --> 00:24:49.636
Man.

00:24:50.637 --> 00:24:51.805
HARDWARE DREAM TREE STATIONERY
Byeong-nam!

00:24:52.806 --> 00:24:53.849
What now?

00:24:54.891 --> 00:24:57.352
How are you feeling?

00:24:57.769 --> 00:25:01.106
Don't you see me making deliveries
right after getting discharged?

00:25:01.189 --> 00:25:02.983
Discharged? When were you admitted?

00:25:03.066 --> 00:25:05.319
This morning! Why didn't you come?

00:25:05.402 --> 00:25:08.780
You got admitted and discharged
in just one morning?

00:25:10.282 --> 00:25:11.658
You're sick.

00:25:12.659 --> 00:25:13.493
Sick?

00:25:14.077 --> 00:25:15.412
You ate it up.

00:25:16.872 --> 00:25:18.498
Who taught you new slang words?

00:25:19.166 --> 00:25:20.834
Whatever. Anyway,

00:25:20.917 --> 00:25:22.961
my wife is in a bad mood today,
so don't come to our store.

00:25:23.045 --> 00:25:24.504
Go to the convenience store
if you need anything.

00:25:24.713 --> 00:25:27.382
Stop going behind her back like that.
That's why she scolds you.

00:25:27.466 --> 00:25:29.593
Go before she gets even angrier. Go.

00:25:29.676 --> 00:25:31.345
What do you say? A drink tonight?

00:25:31.762 --> 00:25:33.513
- Sure, go.
- You down?

00:25:33.597 --> 00:25:36.475
- Sure.
- Okay, sick.

00:25:36.558 --> 00:25:38.560
Just get going already.

00:25:39.770 --> 00:25:42.522
Call me for a drink later, okay?

00:25:48.153 --> 00:25:49.321
You're pathetic.

00:25:57.037 --> 00:25:58.121
CAR INSURANCE CERTIFICATE

00:25:58.205 --> 00:26:00.540
CAR OWNER INFORMATION

00:26:23.772 --> 00:26:25.691
Why am I so good at my job?

00:26:25.774 --> 00:26:28.902
It's not even lunchtime yet,
and I've already handled two cases.

00:26:29.736 --> 00:26:31.780
That's who I am, Boss.

00:26:32.197 --> 00:26:33.448
You seem giddy.

00:26:34.157 --> 00:26:35.867
You got Mr. Grasshopper's agreement?

00:26:35.951 --> 00:26:37.244
Of course.

00:26:37.327 --> 00:26:39.454
I got him confessing
about moving between three hospitals

00:26:39.538 --> 00:26:42.916
and about his special ability
to use his mind to bring out pain.

00:26:43.000 --> 00:26:44.293
It's all in here.

00:26:44.376 --> 00:26:46.712
Special ability?
Is he claiming to be mentally ill now?

00:26:47.045 --> 00:26:48.922
No, it's not like that.

00:26:49.172 --> 00:26:53.135
But if he did that,
I wouldn't let him off the hook easily.

00:26:53.343 --> 00:26:56.138
You know me. I don't let anything slide.

00:26:57.431 --> 00:26:59.182
Is this the accident site?

00:26:59.975 --> 00:27:02.102
There wasn't anything this morning
on my way to work.

00:27:03.103 --> 00:27:05.022
Huh? You don't drive through here
to get to work.

00:27:06.064 --> 00:27:07.899
I moved.

00:27:07.983 --> 00:27:10.944
To the neighborhood up there.
I told you last time.

00:27:12.571 --> 00:27:14.573
That neighborhood
is getting all the attention nowadays.

00:27:17.326 --> 00:27:20.746
It was your wife's idea, wasn't it?

00:27:21.038 --> 00:27:23.540
So, how much do you think
you'll earn from the property?

00:27:26.043 --> 00:27:30.380
That's only for my wife to know.
I know nothing.

00:27:30.464 --> 00:27:31.673
Man, let go.

00:27:31.757 --> 00:27:34.718
I just pack and unpack as I'm told.

00:27:36.261 --> 00:27:37.763
What are you looking for?

00:27:37.971 --> 00:27:39.348
Anything odd.

00:27:40.766 --> 00:27:46.313
Why were they in such a rush
to clean it all up in an hour?

00:27:46.897 --> 00:27:48.482
The car exploded.

00:27:49.149 --> 00:27:51.443
They must've cleaned it up
because the fragments were a hazard.

00:27:52.694 --> 00:27:54.112
You know what's really fishy?

00:27:55.072 --> 00:27:57.991
There's nothing
on the other car or the driver.

00:27:58.075 --> 00:28:01.703
No idea whether they're alive or dead.
But the other car is more at fault.

00:28:03.205 --> 00:28:04.831
Was it not caught
on the dashcam from our side?

00:28:04.915 --> 00:28:09.503
There's no dashcam or anything.
Everything was shattered.

00:28:10.504 --> 00:28:12.130
You can take this case.

00:28:14.758 --> 00:28:15.801
Me?

00:28:15.884 --> 00:28:17.302
You live nearby.

00:28:17.803 --> 00:28:19.888
That's not a good reason to take a case.

00:28:20.555 --> 00:28:24.476
Sang-guk is
in charge of site investigations.

00:28:24.559 --> 00:28:27.729
Sang-guk is on five cases right now.

00:28:28.522 --> 00:28:32.109
Use your special ability or whatever
to trace the other car and its driver.

00:28:32.192 --> 00:28:34.945
That ability isn't mine!
Have you even been listening?

00:28:39.783 --> 00:28:40.867
Man.

00:28:56.842 --> 00:28:59.386
- Dismiss us already.
- Come on!

00:29:00.804 --> 00:29:03.765
- What is it?
- That's still better.

00:29:04.224 --> 00:29:06.226
Hello, this is Min-seo's mom.

00:29:06.310 --> 00:29:08.812
Let's do the level test at the store
instead of at home.

00:29:08.895 --> 00:29:10.606
I can't leave the store unoccupied.

00:29:11.273 --> 00:29:13.025
Yes, ma'am.

00:29:13.108 --> 00:29:14.318
Everyone.

00:29:15.736 --> 00:29:19.323
There won't be a discharge ceremony,
as the Battalion Commander is at his base.

00:29:22.117 --> 00:29:24.870
You're excused once you complete the drill
that was canceled due to rain yesterday.

00:29:25.537 --> 00:29:26.872
Hey, a drink after this?

00:29:27.456 --> 00:29:28.957
I have to go for Min-seo's level test.

00:29:29.041 --> 00:29:31.918
Come on. Let's drink. Please?

00:29:32.002 --> 00:29:33.045
After.

00:29:33.295 --> 00:29:35.339
There's no discharge ceremony,
and this is the last drill,

00:29:35.422 --> 00:29:38.050
so let's have you
disassemble and assemble guns.

00:29:38.133 --> 00:29:39.593
TRAINING RESERVED FORCES
TO SERVE THE NATION

00:29:39.676 --> 00:29:41.303
- Come on!
- It's the last task.

00:29:41.386 --> 00:29:42.429
A gun?

00:29:42.512 --> 00:29:45.682
Should we make a bet
to make you focus better?

00:29:46.350 --> 00:29:50.354
I'll let you out early
if you're better than our trainer, okay?

00:29:50.771 --> 00:29:52.940
- Sweet!
- You said you were good!

00:29:53.315 --> 00:29:55.525
Do you remember how to do that?

00:29:58.070 --> 00:29:59.279
What are you doing?

00:29:59.696 --> 00:30:01.490
HOW TO DISASSEMBLE AND ASSEMBLE A K2 RIFLE

00:30:04.201 --> 00:30:07.663
Sir, will you really let us off early
if we beat the trainer?

00:30:08.914 --> 00:30:11.875
He's the fastest in our battalion.
Are you sure?

00:30:14.503 --> 00:30:15.671
He accepts the challenge!

00:30:18.131 --> 00:30:19.091
Are you kidding me?

00:30:23.804 --> 00:30:25.430
- You still got it!
- Let's go!

00:30:26.056 --> 00:30:27.140
Ready,

00:30:27.599 --> 00:30:29.810
set, go!

00:30:49.621 --> 00:30:52.416
Fifty-eight seconds. A new record.

00:30:55.043 --> 00:30:56.586
You're insane, Jeong-hwan!

00:30:57.170 --> 00:30:59.089
Totally insane! Awesome!

00:31:00.716 --> 00:31:02.009
You did it!

00:31:15.897 --> 00:31:17.357
You'd better pay for the beer today.

00:31:17.482 --> 00:31:18.692
No!

00:31:18.775 --> 00:31:20.652
- Get out, then.
- Sorry.

00:31:27.159 --> 00:31:28.368
It's like we're on a trip.

00:31:40.505 --> 00:31:45.010
KINDERGARTEN

00:31:50.307 --> 00:31:52.059
SPECIAL MARTIAL ARTS YONGMU GYM

00:31:52.142 --> 00:31:54.019
- Hello.
- Hello.

00:31:54.102 --> 00:31:56.438
Stand straight! Salute to the master.

00:31:56.521 --> 00:31:57.814
- Salute!
- Salute!

00:31:57.898 --> 00:31:59.650
- Salute!
- Welcome.

00:31:59.733 --> 00:32:01.443
- Come in.
- Get in.

00:32:01.526 --> 00:32:02.903
- Hello, Master.
- Hello.

00:32:02.986 --> 00:32:04.613
Watch your steps.

00:32:05.405 --> 00:32:06.239
Be careful.

00:32:06.949 --> 00:32:09.534
Hello, you're a new face.

00:32:10.077 --> 00:32:12.621
- She's a new student starting today.
- Is she?

00:32:12.704 --> 00:32:13.872
What's your name?

00:32:13.956 --> 00:32:15.165
Choi Do-yeon.

00:32:15.248 --> 00:32:16.625
I see, Do-yeon.

00:32:16.708 --> 00:32:21.838
You'd have so much fun
training with your friends after class.

00:32:23.048 --> 00:32:26.593
Make sure to ask your mom to sign you up
when you go home, okay?

00:32:28.971 --> 00:32:31.264
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

00:32:44.194 --> 00:32:45.445
Dad!

00:32:45.737 --> 00:32:46.947
Hey!

00:32:48.824 --> 00:32:50.534
You're right on time.

00:32:58.959 --> 00:33:00.419
Hello!

00:33:00.836 --> 00:33:03.672
I'm right on time.
I was ten seconds too early.

00:33:05.799 --> 00:33:06.883
Sure.

00:33:06.967 --> 00:33:08.719
See you tomorrow, Do-yeon.

00:33:08.802 --> 00:33:11.096
Bye. Goodbye, sir.

00:33:11.179 --> 00:33:13.515
- Thank you.
- Bye.

00:33:16.310 --> 00:33:19.271
How was the new kindergarten?
Did you have fun with your new friends?

00:33:19.354 --> 00:33:21.690
Yes, we made stuffed bunnies.

00:33:22.024 --> 00:33:25.569
Dad, I want to go to the martial arts gym
instead of ballet.

00:33:26.445 --> 00:33:27.946
- A martial arts gym?
- Yes.

00:33:28.030 --> 00:33:31.241
All my friends left in the gym van,
except me.

00:33:32.784 --> 00:33:33.785
I see.

00:33:37.080 --> 00:33:40.500
SPECIAL MARTIAL ARTS YONGMU GYM

00:33:40.709 --> 00:33:44.004
Focus!

00:33:44.338 --> 00:33:47.841
If you die,
you're a liability to your team!

00:33:47.924 --> 00:33:49.092
Jump!

00:33:52.638 --> 00:33:55.307
Watch out for your comrades!
Or else, they'll die!

00:33:55.390 --> 00:33:56.516
Jump!

00:34:00.646 --> 00:34:02.731
I'm sorry, my comrades.

00:34:04.358 --> 00:34:05.275
Let me up.

00:34:05.359 --> 00:34:07.778
- Okay.
- Let's go again!

00:34:07.861 --> 00:34:09.446
Do-yeon is here! Are you her father?

00:34:09.529 --> 00:34:10.822
Where are you going?

00:34:10.906 --> 00:34:13.367
Okay, let me go!

00:34:13.825 --> 00:34:14.910
Ready!

00:34:16.703 --> 00:34:17.996
Kick one!

00:34:20.624 --> 00:34:21.875
Kick two!

00:34:24.252 --> 00:34:25.379
Kick three!

00:34:25.504 --> 00:34:27.089
As you can see,

00:34:27.172 --> 00:34:30.384
it's excellent for increasing stamina
and stimulating growth.

00:34:30.467 --> 00:34:31.551
Kick two!

00:34:31.635 --> 00:34:34.554
And our classes are all about having fun,

00:34:34.638 --> 00:34:36.181
so kids really love it here.

