00:50:42.564 --> 00:50:44.691
Are you the new neighbor
in the next building?

00:50:46.985 --> 00:50:48.236
What are you doing here?

00:50:49.112 --> 00:50:51.239
You said you were going on a patrol.

00:50:52.658 --> 00:50:54.910
Yes, I'm back now.

00:50:55.494 --> 00:50:57.204
Did you come to get me?

00:50:57.496 --> 00:50:59.873
- Let's head in.
- Okay.

00:50:59.957 --> 00:51:01.541
- Bye, then.
- We'll head in.

00:51:01.625 --> 00:51:05.087
- Goodnight.
- I told you to stay in.

00:51:05.963 --> 00:51:07.339
Let's head in.

00:51:08.924 --> 00:51:11.426
Her symptoms are pretty serious.

00:51:14.930 --> 00:51:16.431
Is she unwell?

00:51:20.894 --> 00:51:22.312
No, my point is,

00:51:23.063 --> 00:51:26.108
she's not the type
to play with a stuffed bunny,

00:51:26.191 --> 00:51:29.319
and she's also not the type
to toss trash just anywhere.

00:51:30.320 --> 00:51:32.322
Yes, even I could tell that.

00:51:34.616 --> 00:51:37.119
Are you suspecting me right now?

00:51:37.786 --> 00:51:39.538
If it's not you, who would it be?

00:51:40.122 --> 00:51:43.041
Are you kidding me? Do you know who I am?

00:51:43.125 --> 00:51:44.668
Do I need to know that
to get recycling done?

00:51:44.751 --> 00:51:47.212
Do I seem like the type to cut open
a stuffed animal's belly?

00:51:47.296 --> 00:51:48.297
How did you know about the belly?

00:51:48.588 --> 00:51:50.757
Because I just saw it!

00:51:50.841 --> 00:51:52.592
- This is...
- Okay.

00:51:52.676 --> 00:51:53.760
Look at it again.

00:52:01.435 --> 00:52:03.145
What is it? What's wrong?

00:52:05.147 --> 00:52:08.317
I think there's cat hair inside.
I'm allergic.

00:52:10.527 --> 00:52:11.945
There's no cat hair.

00:52:12.988 --> 00:52:14.364
You're allergic?

00:52:14.865 --> 00:52:17.075
That's too bad.

00:52:17.159 --> 00:52:18.785
Oh, no.

00:52:20.037 --> 00:52:22.497
You'd better recycle properly from now on.

00:52:22.581 --> 00:52:25.334
I'm watching you, okay?

00:52:26.335 --> 00:52:27.544
Seriously.

00:52:34.635 --> 00:52:36.386
Why do you keep following me?

00:52:36.470 --> 00:52:38.055
Who? Me?

00:52:38.138 --> 00:52:39.973
I'm just going home this way.

00:52:40.057 --> 00:52:42.684
Why are you walking this way
when you live there?

00:52:43.393 --> 00:52:44.519
Out of guilt?

00:52:44.603 --> 00:52:46.229
Guilt for what?

00:52:46.313 --> 00:52:48.398
I'm just going to the convenience store
to get cigarettes.

00:52:48.482 --> 00:52:51.902
Remember, cigarettes go in regular waste.

00:52:51.985 --> 00:52:54.363
It's a 50,000-won fine
if you discard it on the streets.

00:52:54.446 --> 00:52:56.239
In some cases, they even arrest you.

00:52:56.323 --> 00:52:59.034
Why are you following me around
and nagging me? What did I do?

00:53:00.118 --> 00:53:01.870
You know,

00:53:02.287 --> 00:53:04.665
it's just that I found two black bags
of tattered stuffed bunnies,

00:53:04.748 --> 00:53:07.876
once in the morning, and once at night.

00:53:07.960 --> 00:53:10.128
And you just happened
to move in yesterday.

00:53:10.587 --> 00:53:12.673
And both were spotted
at the dumpster near your building.

00:53:12.965 --> 00:53:16.343
Even more, you had the second bag
in your own hands.

00:53:16.426 --> 00:53:18.303
And you have a kid
who has stuffed animals.

00:53:18.679 --> 00:53:20.347
Isn't that suspicious?

00:53:20.973 --> 00:53:24.559
If it isn't, what in the world is?

00:53:24.893 --> 00:53:26.061
Goodness.

00:53:27.270 --> 00:53:30.065
You're crazy. You're out of your mind.

00:53:31.233 --> 00:53:33.902
If you want to suspect someone,
bring evidence.

00:53:33.986 --> 00:53:35.445
But you wouldn't be able to get any.

00:53:35.529 --> 00:53:37.406
Why? Because I didn't do it.

00:53:39.783 --> 00:53:42.286
Why am I even explaining this to you?

00:53:44.204 --> 00:53:45.580
Maybe you're guilty.

00:53:59.845 --> 00:54:02.472
What? My gosh, what are you doing?

00:54:02.973 --> 00:54:04.975
- It's him.
- Who?

00:54:05.058 --> 00:54:06.893
The man who just left the store.

00:54:06.977 --> 00:54:08.478
He was at the dumpster earlier.

00:54:08.562 --> 00:54:10.355
- Let's go and ask him.
- Ask him what?

00:54:10.439 --> 00:54:13.525
He would've seen me get there later!

00:54:15.110 --> 00:54:16.987
Hey, wait.

00:54:17.321 --> 00:54:18.447
- Hey!
- Run!

00:54:23.702 --> 00:54:26.079
Excuse me, can I talk to you?

00:54:27.956 --> 00:54:29.124
I need to ask you something.

00:54:32.127 --> 00:54:33.086
What?

00:54:34.421 --> 00:54:36.840
What is it? What?

00:54:37.507 --> 00:54:40.010
Hey! I'm not dangerous or anything!

00:54:41.386 --> 00:54:42.304
Sir.

00:54:43.680 --> 00:54:44.806
You're kidding.

00:54:45.390 --> 00:54:46.683
Hey, wait!

00:54:47.768 --> 00:54:48.894
Be careful!

00:54:56.318 --> 00:54:57.694
What did he just do?

00:54:58.570 --> 00:54:59.404
Darn it.

00:55:09.998 --> 00:55:12.501
How can he run so well in sliders?

00:55:12.584 --> 00:55:14.294
It's way too late for this nonsense.

00:55:28.433 --> 00:55:29.518
Excuse me!

00:55:29.601 --> 00:55:31.478
Stop right there!

00:55:33.647 --> 00:55:35.941
- Sir!
- Why is he so damn fast?

00:55:37.359 --> 00:55:38.277
Hey!

00:55:41.488 --> 00:55:42.489
Excuse me!

00:55:43.407 --> 00:55:44.408
Darn it!

00:55:44.908 --> 00:55:46.493
It's uphill from there.

00:55:50.163 --> 00:55:50.998
Excuse me!

00:55:52.374 --> 00:55:53.208
Hey!

00:56:00.632 --> 00:56:02.092
Oh, my. Sir!

00:56:02.175 --> 00:56:04.136
- Out of my way!
- Sir!

00:56:10.934 --> 00:56:14.730
I just want to ask you something! Stop it!

00:56:24.156 --> 00:56:25.532
Darn it!

00:56:29.161 --> 00:56:30.037
Hey!

00:56:30.954 --> 00:56:31.913
Sir!

00:56:33.457 --> 00:56:34.458
Excuse me!

00:56:35.542 --> 00:56:36.418
Excuse me!

00:56:38.962 --> 00:56:39.838
Sir!

00:56:56.772 --> 00:56:57.773
Where did he go?

00:56:58.607 --> 00:57:00.692
Where is he?

00:57:02.986 --> 00:57:04.029
Sir!

00:57:04.529 --> 00:57:06.073
Are you kidding me right now?

00:57:06.156 --> 00:57:07.074
Excuse me!

00:57:08.617 --> 00:57:10.243
My gosh!

00:57:11.828 --> 00:57:13.413
There's nowhere else for you to go.

00:57:13.664 --> 00:57:14.831
This is the rooftop.

00:57:40.023 --> 00:57:41.942
I just wanted to ask you something!

00:57:42.025 --> 00:57:43.860
Why do you keep running away?

00:57:43.944 --> 00:57:45.737
My gosh, my sliders are all ruined.

00:57:52.869 --> 00:57:54.037
MK2?

00:57:59.251 --> 00:58:01.169
Who are you? That's dangerous.

00:58:10.637 --> 00:58:11.638
Are you a foreigner?

00:58:50.135 --> 00:58:51.595
My goodness!

00:58:53.764 --> 00:58:56.350
Man! My heart is about to burst.

00:58:56.975 --> 00:58:58.101
Where did he go?

00:58:58.352 --> 00:59:00.354
- That way.
- That way?

00:59:01.563 --> 00:59:03.899
You said you had something to ask him.
Did you ask him?

00:59:07.402 --> 00:59:08.278
Did you get into a fight?

00:59:10.364 --> 00:59:11.531
Oh, yes.

00:59:11.990 --> 00:59:14.076
He went that way,
but I don't see him anymore.

00:59:15.035 --> 00:59:16.453
I'd better go home.

00:59:18.038 --> 00:59:19.039
That's the main road.

00:59:20.916 --> 00:59:22.042
What?

00:59:22.125 --> 00:59:23.627
It's a long detour.

00:59:23.710 --> 00:59:25.629
This way is faster.

00:59:25.963 --> 00:59:28.215
You can't lead the way
when you know nothing.

00:59:29.299 --> 00:59:31.176
Why didn't you come sooner
if you knew your way so well?

00:59:31.259 --> 00:59:33.428
You came after everything,
and here you are, boasting.

00:59:33.679 --> 00:59:36.056
I ran as fast as I could, too.

00:59:37.933 --> 00:59:40.435
Follow me or go the long way.

00:59:41.895 --> 00:59:43.105
My knees are killing me.

00:59:50.279 --> 00:59:51.196
Wait for me.

01:00:34.698 --> 01:00:38.702
Did you hear a gunshot? With a muffler.

01:00:39.244 --> 01:00:40.329
A gunshot?

01:00:40.704 --> 01:00:44.333
Why are you so startled?
We see guns all the time in the army.

01:00:45.042 --> 01:00:46.335
I was exempt from service.

01:00:47.419 --> 01:00:48.754
No wonder.

01:00:49.671 --> 01:00:50.839
You're so out of it.

01:00:51.465 --> 01:00:54.551
Out of what? I was much faster than you.

01:00:54.635 --> 01:00:57.054
Why were you exempt from service
if you were so fast, then?

01:00:57.512 --> 01:01:00.849
You couldn't even catch that tiny guy,
and you're a mess.

01:01:01.099 --> 01:01:02.851
You could've just gone in, and...

01:01:05.187 --> 01:01:06.897
This was all you needed to do.

01:01:07.314 --> 01:01:09.733
You don't know how to do this
because you didn't serve in the army.

01:01:10.150 --> 01:01:12.861
What are you, five years old?

01:01:12.986 --> 01:01:16.156
Why are you being so rude?

01:01:16.782 --> 01:01:20.285
I just can't talk to men
who haven't served.

01:01:34.299 --> 01:01:37.678
JOWOONG BANK

01:01:41.640 --> 01:01:42.516
What is he doing?

01:01:44.977 --> 01:01:46.311
What is it now?

01:01:51.566 --> 01:01:53.360
ENTER YOUR PASSCODE

01:01:53.443 --> 01:01:54.444
CHOOSE YOUR TRANSACTION

01:01:54.528 --> 01:01:56.905
AMOUNT: 101,571,879 WON

01:02:06.290 --> 01:02:08.333
- What are you looking at?
- My gosh!

01:02:08.417 --> 01:02:10.502
Why are you zoning out here alone?

01:02:10.585 --> 01:02:13.046
Aren't you going to go home?
Don't follow me, and go home.

01:02:13.130 --> 01:02:14.131
Just go.

01:02:14.214 --> 01:02:17.134
Why do you care about where I go?

01:02:17.301 --> 01:02:19.678
You keep getting more and more suspicious.

01:02:20.929 --> 01:02:21.763
What now?

01:02:23.515 --> 01:02:25.976
Hey, it's him.

01:02:26.059 --> 01:02:28.437
- It's him, isn't he?
- No.

01:02:28.520 --> 01:02:31.148
I'll go in alone and talk to him.
Good work tonight.

01:02:31.231 --> 01:02:32.858
- You can go.
- What? We can go together.

01:02:32.941 --> 01:02:35.652
No, I told you to go! Just leave!

01:02:38.488 --> 01:02:40.782
You think you can tell me what to do?

01:02:41.366 --> 01:02:43.243
I'm the youth association president
in this neighborhood.

01:02:43.994 --> 01:02:46.038
Hey! What a ridiculous guy.

01:02:46.121 --> 01:02:47.289
Just go!

01:02:47.372 --> 01:02:48.874
ENTER THE RECIPIENT ACCOUNT NUMBER

01:02:48.957 --> 01:02:50.042
I told you to leave!

01:02:50.125 --> 01:02:51.376
You said we should go ask him!

01:02:56.923 --> 01:02:58.175
I told you to leave!

01:02:58.258 --> 01:02:59.718
Let's go together!

01:03:15.859 --> 01:03:16.735
Watch out!

01:03:56.441 --> 01:04:02.447
SECOND EXPLOSION
ON AUG 17, 2025 AT 12:30 A.M.

01:04:11.248 --> 01:04:14.418
What exploded, Officer Park?

01:04:15.002 --> 01:04:16.461
Please just go to bed.

01:04:16.920 --> 01:04:20.590
I was just crossing the street
when it exploded

01:04:20.674 --> 01:04:22.134
and threw me to the ground.

01:04:22.551 --> 01:04:24.803
I was too shocked to notice anything.

01:04:25.429 --> 01:04:27.639
Yes, you can ask that guy.

01:04:29.975 --> 01:04:31.059
Let me sanitize your wound.

01:04:33.312 --> 01:04:34.855
I haven't done anything.

01:04:35.564 --> 01:04:37.024
It hurts so much.

01:04:37.107 --> 01:04:39.151
Just the smell of it makes it sting.

01:04:42.195 --> 01:04:44.948
- I'd like to ask you some questions.
- Sure.

01:04:45.032 --> 01:04:47.784
Do you remember anything
about the man inside?

01:04:49.995 --> 01:04:52.998
He was a foreigner.
Maybe Southeast Asian...

01:04:53.832 --> 01:04:56.835
No, South American? Or Russian?

01:04:56.918 --> 01:04:59.379
I'm not sure about his exact ethnicity.

01:04:59.463 --> 01:05:02.966
I needed to ask him something,
so I tried to talk to him.

01:05:03.050 --> 01:05:06.345
But he kept glancing at me
before running away.

01:05:06.428 --> 01:05:09.681
I wondered why he was running,
so I ran after him.

01:05:09.765 --> 01:05:13.560
But the man suddenly started
waving a knife at me!

01:05:13.644 --> 01:05:15.646
- A knife?
- Yes!

01:05:15.729 --> 01:05:17.689
It was a knife at first,
but then, he whipped out a gun...

01:05:18.357 --> 01:05:19.274
A gun?

01:05:24.321 --> 01:05:28.951
I mean, he whipped out his big guns
and started pounding on me.

01:05:29.826 --> 01:05:31.286
Then he ran away.

01:05:31.995 --> 01:05:36.124
Did you see what he was doing
in the ATM booth?

01:05:36.208 --> 01:05:37.542
Well...

01:05:45.133 --> 01:05:46.093
Military boots?

01:05:47.135 --> 01:05:50.305
He was probably withdrawing some money.

01:05:54.893 --> 01:05:56.812
ARMY18 8285

01:05:56.895 --> 01:05:58.063
A military van?

01:06:06.196 --> 01:06:07.239
Soldiers?

01:06:47.362 --> 01:06:50.282
HEROES NEXT DOOR

01:06:50.365 --> 01:06:54.870
The guilty always return to the scene.

01:06:54.953 --> 01:06:56.163
What is this place?

01:06:56.246 --> 01:06:58.624
He took the damaged car
and drove toward Hanbal Mountain.

01:06:58.707 --> 01:07:01.293
A butane gas explosion caused a death.

01:07:01.376 --> 01:07:03.003
Butane gas? Are you serious?

01:07:03.086 --> 01:07:04.421
I can't stand this!

01:07:04.504 --> 01:07:06.298
They're trying to cover this up.

01:07:06.381 --> 01:07:09.259
There's something going on here.

01:07:10.510 --> 01:07:12.429
So he's a secret agent for the NIS?

01:07:13.263 --> 01:07:14.723
I think Choi Kang is

01:07:16.016 --> 01:07:17.309
a North Korean spy.

01:07:18.977 --> 01:07:20.979
Subtitle translation by Min-sun Kim